        <mxCell id="6cDqBenDorvTYhrIJY9u-1" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;S64(1)(iv) &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Income From assets transferred to spouse&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Individual transfers assets other than house property for no consideration or inadequate consideration to spouse, then such income in the hands of spouse will be clubbed and taxable in the hands of individual.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. assets need not be retained in the same form&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;for e.g. if individual gifts money to spouse and spouse &lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;buy shares, income from CG will be clubbed to individual.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; transfers can also be indirect&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;individual t/f shares to spouse, spouse transfers &lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;debentures&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;in this case deb will be taxable in the hands of spouse&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;and shares will be taxable in the hands of individual&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;arcSize=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
